  "prompt": "What are common early pregnancy symptoms or signs that make you feel you may be pregnant?",
  "response": "Common early pregnancy symptoms include:\n\n1. Missed period\n2. Mild spotting or implantation bleeding\n3. Breast tenderness or swelling\n4. Fatigue or increased tiredness\n5. Nausea or morning sickness\n6. Frequent urination\n7. Food cravings or aversions\n8. Mood swings\n9. Mild cramping\n10. Increased sense of smell\n11. Headaches\n12. Bloating\n13. Light-headedness\n14. Constipation\n15. Raised basal body temperature\n\nHowever, these symptoms can vary greatly between individuals, and the only way to confirm pregnancy is through a pregnancy test or medical examination.",
